---
description: Applies to Supabase, database, auth, and rating data work
globs:
  - "supabase/**/*.sql"
  - "supabase/**/*"
  - "src/lib/supabase*"
  - "src/features/**/*.ts"
  - "src/features/**/*.tsx"
---

Before database changes, read:
- `docs/DATA_MODEL.md`
- `docs/API_CONTRACTS.md`
- `docs/DOCUMENTATION_POLICY.md`

Rules:
- Use relational Supabase tables.
- Do not create one giant product JSON object.
- Do not change schema without updating `docs/DATA_MODEL.md`.
- Products, images, offers, Eazy Scores, and rating summaries should be publicly readable.
- Users can only insert/update/delete their own ratings.
- Trusted Community Score recalculation must happen with database trigger/function or server-side logic.
- Never expose service-role keys in client code.
- Do not implement scraping until the mock core app flow works.
- Supabase, auth, RLS, schema, or API-contract changes must update affected docs before commit/PR handoff.
